snippet.textDisplay:
From a British citizen perspective- It is absolutely depressing to know that Harry and Meg are leaving as they were a the breath of fresh air that we needed. 95% of the British press are crap and some are racist (like The Sun and The Daily Mail- thank god I read the I, an independent newspaper who isn’t funded to support parties) but what they did the most is just degraded Megan and Harry so far with silly issues like family disputes, bro v bro conflicts and constant press coverage (not like we all don’t argue with our families or something)... - the press wasn’t so much racist to Megan but just absolutely degraded her so that when they did use racism it wasn’t recognisable to the ‘ordinary reader’ of magazines and right wing media. It just became so normal for that readership to acknowledge as true like Corbyn being a Marxist.

I feel sorry and I hope they can recoup in Canada and get their HMH’s back again. But although I do like Megan it does seem like she’s up to something and that the conflicts between her and Kate are true. The issue is whether- she’s going to take Harry to far with Canada and the American Press. I hope that she doesn’t as she did want to go to LA not Canada which hasn’t been a good move for royals (eg Mrs Simpson and his highness Edward VIII). And after all when Kate asked if she needed any help within the first few weeks of settling in to the family- she rejected bluntly. And now they’re selling the ‘Sussex’ name as a brand without the Queen’s permission- selling a royal title is disgraceful no matter what it is. You shouldn’t sell it for profit- it’s a name that you respect and protect. And that’s why I’m worried about Megan- as she might think that everything, titles and all, are for sell and profit. We’re not LA. And you’re not an actress anymore you’re a part of a royal family. It reminds me of Mrs Simpson...

It does seem that Americans don’t get on well with the royals, like it’s some sort of curse... despite my support for Megan and Harry- it’s seems to be a reply of Simpson and Edward part 2 and selling the Sussex name is just wrong. Sell your own name... the Sussex name is something which is inherited from one generation to the next. Not something sold off for short term profit. Maybe both of them need a break yes- but maybe they need to think what’s morally right and what’s the wrong thing to do in their roles.

And let’s face it the hardest done by from Megexit is William as he now has to cope with no brother and all the responsibility of the future generation on his shoulders- yet he was always there for Harry, thick and thin. I just feel for him as much as I do for Harry and Megan.

snippet.textDisplay: Here in North America we grow up believing that all British people are super posh and elegant, which is why it was so shocking for me to learn how obsessed the UK is with tabloids and celebrity gossip. Even their TV is all trashy reality shows, and they lap it up over there. People have so many stereotypes about Americans being low-brow and unsophisticated, but as a Canadian who has been to both countries, I honestly think the UK fits that stereotype just as well if not better. You can criticize the concept of monarchy as much as you want, but you'd think people would have some respect for people's personal lives after Diana. But whether it's the royal family, or the clowns on their reality TV shows, or celebrities, or their own neighbours, revelling in people's personal misfortunes and spreading gossip around seems to be a huge part of the culture over there.
